var book = {
	"name": "Proverbs",
	"numChapters": 31,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>These are the proverbs of Solomon, David’s son, king of Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Their purpose is to teach people wisdom and discipline,to help them understand the insights of the wise.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Their purpose is to teach people to live disciplined and successful lives,to help them do what is right, just, and fair.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>These proverbs will give insight to the simple,knowledge and discernment to the young.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Let the wise listen to these proverbs and become even wiser.Let those with understanding receive guidance",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>by exploring the meaning in these proverbs and parables,the words of the wise and their riddles.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Fear of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is the foundation of true knowledge,but fools despise wisdom and discipline.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>My child, listen when your father corrects you.Don’t neglect your mother’s instruction.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>What you learn from them will crown you with graceand be a chain of honor around your neck.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>My child, if sinners entice you,turn your back on them!",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>They may say, “Come and join us.Let’s hide and kill someone!Just for fun, let’s ambush the innocent!",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Let’s swallow them alive, like the grave;let’s swallow them whole, like those who go down to the pit of death.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Think of the great things we’ll get!We’ll fill our houses with all the stuff we take.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Come, throw in your lot with us;we’ll all share the loot.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>My child, don’t go along with them!Stay far away from their paths.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>They rush to commit evil deeds.They hurry to commit murder.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>If a bird sees a trap being set,it knows to stay away.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But these people set an ambush for themselves;they are trying to get themselves killed.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Such is the fate of all who are greedy for money;it robs them of life.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Wisdom shouts in the streets.She cries out in the public square.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>She calls to the crowds along the main street,to those gathered in front of the city gate:",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“How long, you simpletons,will you insist on being simpleminded?How long will you mockers relish your mocking?How long will you fools hate knowledge?",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Come and listen to my counsel.I’ll share my heart with youand make you wise.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“I called you so often, but you wouldn’t come.I reached out to you, but you paid no attention.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>You ignored my adviceand rejected the correction I offered.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So I will laugh when you are in trouble!I will mock you when disaster overtakes you—",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>when calamity overtakes you like a storm,when disaster engulfs you like a cyclone,and anguish and distress overwhelm you.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“When they cry for help, I will not answer.Though they anxiously search for me, they will not find me.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>For they hated knowledgeand chose not to fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>They rejected my adviceand paid no attention when I corrected them.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Therefore, they must eat the bitter fruit of living their own way,choking on their own schemes.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>For simpletons turn away from me—to death.Fools are destroyed by their own complacency.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>But all who listen to me will live in peace,untroubled by fear of harm.”"
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>My child, listen to what I say,and treasure my commands.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Tune your ears to wisdom,and concentrate on understanding.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Cry out for insight,and ask for understanding.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Search for them as you would for silver;seek them like hidden treasures.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then you will understand what it means to fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,and you will gain knowledge of God.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> grants wisdom!From his mouth come knowledge and understanding.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He grants a treasure of common sense to the honest.He is a shield to those who walk with integrity.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He guards the paths of the justand protects those who are faithful to him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then you will understand what is right, just, and fair,and you will find the right way to go.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For wisdom will enter your heart,and knowledge will fill you with joy.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Wise choices will watch over you.Understanding will keep you safe.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Wisdom will save you from evil people,from those whose words are twisted.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>These men turn from the right wayto walk down dark paths.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They take pleasure in doing wrong,and they enjoy the twisted ways of evil.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Their actions are crooked,and their ways are wrong.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Wisdom will save you from the immoral woman,from the seductive words of the promiscuous woman.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>She has abandoned her husbandand ignores the covenant she made before God.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Entering her house leads to death;it is the road to the grave.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The man who visits her is doomed.He will never reach the paths of life.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So follow the steps of the good,and stay on the paths of the righteous.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>For only the godly will live in the land,and those with integrity will remain in it.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But the wicked will be removed from the land,and the treacherous will be uprooted."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>My child, never forget the things I have taught you.Store my commands in your heart.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>If you do this, you will live many years,and your life will be satisfying.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Never let loyalty and kindness leave you!Tie them around your neck as a reminder.Write them deep within your heart.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then you will find favor with both God and people,and you will earn a good reputation.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Trust in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with all your heart;do not depend on your own understanding.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Seek his will in all you do,and he will show you which path to take.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Don’t be impressed with your own wisdom.Instead, fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and turn away from evil.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then you will have healing for your bodyand strength for your bones.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Honor the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with your wealthand with the best part of everything you produce.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then he will fill your barns with grain,and your vats will overflow with good wine.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>My child, don’t reject the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s discipline,and don’t be upset when he corrects you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> corrects those he loves,just as a father corrects a child in whom he delights.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Joyful is the person who finds wisdom,the one who gains understanding.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For wisdom is more profitable than silver,and her wages are better than gold.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Wisdom is more precious than rubies;nothing you desire can compare with her.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>She offers you long life in her right hand,and riches and honor in her left.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>She will guide you down delightful paths;all her ways are satisfying.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Wisdom is a tree of life to those who embrace her;happy are those who hold her tightly.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>By wisdom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> founded the earth;by understanding he created the heavens.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>By his knowledge the deep fountains of the earth burst forth,and the dew settles beneath the night sky.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>My child, don’t lose sight of common sense and discernment.Hang on to them,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>for they will refresh your soul.They are like jewels on a necklace.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>They keep you safe on your way,and your feet will not stumble.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>You can go to bed without fear;you will lie down and sleep soundly.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>You need not be afraid of sudden disasteror the destruction that comes upon the wicked,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is your security.He will keep your foot from being caught in a trap.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Do not withhold good from those who deserve itwhen it’s in your power to help them.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>If you can help your neighbor now, don’t say,“Come back tomorrow, and then I’ll help you.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Don’t plot harm against your neighbor,for those who live nearby trust you.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Don’t pick a fight without reason,when no one has done you harm.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Don’t envy violent peopleor copy their ways.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Such wicked people are detestable to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,but he offers his friendship to the godly.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> curses the house of the wicked,but he blesses the home of the upright.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> mocks the mockersbut is gracious to the humble.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The wise inherit honor,but fools are put to shame!"
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>My children, listen when your father corrects you.Pay attention and learn good judgment,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>for I am giving you good guidance.Don’t turn away from my instructions.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For I, too, was once my father’s son,tenderly loved as my mother’s only child.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>My father taught me,“Take my words to heart.Follow my commands, and you will live.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Get wisdom; develop good judgment.Don’t forget my words or turn away from them.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Don’t turn your back on wisdom, for she will protect you.Love her, and she will guard you.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Getting wisdom is the wisest thing you can do!And whatever else you do, develop good judgment.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>If you prize wisdom, she will make you great.Embrace her, and she will honor you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>She will place a lovely wreath on your head;she will present you with a beautiful crown.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>My child, listen to me and do as I say,and you will have a long, good life.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>I will teach you wisdom’s waysand lead you in straight paths.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When you walk, you won’t be held back;when you run, you won’t stumble.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Take hold of my instructions; don’t let them go.Guard them, for they are the key to life.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Don’t do as the wicked do,and don’t follow the path of evildoers.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Don’t even think about it; don’t go that way.Turn away and keep moving.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For evil people can’t sleep until they’ve done their evil deed for the day.They can’t rest until they’ve caused someone to stumble.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They eat the food of wickednessand drink the wine of violence!",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The way of the righteous is like the first gleam of dawn,which shines ever brighter until the full light of day.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But the way of the wicked is like total darkness.They have no idea what they are stumbling over.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>My child, pay attention to what I say.Listen carefully to my words.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Don’t lose sight of them.Let them penetrate deep into your heart,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>for they bring life to those who find them,and healing to their whole body.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Guard your heart above all else,for it determines the course of your life.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Avoid all perverse talk;stay away from corrupt speech.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Look straight ahead,and fix your eyes on what lies before you.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Mark out a straight path for your feet;stay on the safe path.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Don’t get sidetracked;keep your feet from following evil."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>My son, pay attention to my wisdom;listen carefully to my wise counsel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then you will show discernment,and your lips will express what you’ve learned.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For the lips of an immoral woman are as sweet as honey,and her mouth is smoother than oil.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But in the end she is as bitter as poison,as dangerous as a double-edged sword.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Her feet go down to death;her steps lead straight to the grave.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For she cares nothing about the path to life.She staggers down a crooked trail and doesn’t realize it.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So now, my sons, listen to me.Never stray from what I am about to say:",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Stay away from her!Don’t go near the door of her house!",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>If you do, you will lose your honorand will lose to merciless people all you have achieved.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Strangers will consume your wealth,and someone else will enjoy the fruit of your labor.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>In the end you will groan in anguishwhen disease consumes your body.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>You will say, “How I hated discipline!If only I had not ignored all the warnings!",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Oh, why didn’t I listen to my teachers?Why didn’t I pay attention to my instructors?",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>I have come to the brink of utter ruin,and now I must face public disgrace.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Drink water from your own well—share your love only with your wife.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Why spill the water of your springs in the streets,having sex with just anyone?",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>You should reserve it for yourselves.Never share it with strangers.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Let your wife be a fountain of blessing for you.Rejoice in the wife of your youth.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>She is a loving deer, a graceful doe.Let her breasts satisfy you always.May you always be captivated by her love.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Why be captivated, my son, by an immoral woman,or fondle the breasts of a promiscuous woman?",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sees clearly what a man does,examining every path he takes.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>An evil man is held captive by his own sins;they are ropes that catch and hold him.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He will die for lack of self-control;he will be lost because of his great foolishness."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>My child, if you have put up security for a friend’s debtor agreed to guarantee the debt of a stranger—",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>if you have trapped yourself by your agreementand are caught by what you said—",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>follow my advice and save yourself,for you have placed yourself at your friend’s mercy.Now swallow your pride;go and beg to have your name erased.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Don’t put it off; do it now!Don’t rest until you do.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Save yourself like a gazelle escaping from a hunter,like a bird fleeing from a net.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Take a lesson from the ants, you lazybones.Learn from their ways and become wise!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Though they have no princeor governor or ruler to make them work,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>they labor hard all summer,gathering food for the winter.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But you, lazybones, how long will you sleep?When will you wake up?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>A little extra sleep, a little more slumber,a little folding of the hands to rest—",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>then poverty will pounce on you like a bandit;scarcity will attack you like an armed robber.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>What are worthless and wicked people like?They are constant liars,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>signaling their deceit with a wink of the eye,a nudge of the foot, or the wiggle of fingers.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Their perverted hearts plot evil,and they constantly stir up trouble.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But they will be destroyed suddenly,broken in an instant beyond all hope of healing.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>There are six things the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> hates—no, seven things he detests:",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>haughty eyes,a lying tongue,hands that kill the innocent,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>a heart that plots evil,feet that race to do wrong,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>a false witness who pours out lies,a person who sows discord in a family.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>My son, obey your father’s commands,and don’t neglect your mother’s instruction.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Keep their words always in your heart.Tie them around your neck.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When you walk, their counsel will lead you.When you sleep, they will protect you.When you wake up, they will advise you.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For their command is a lampand their instruction a light;their corrective disciplineis the way to life.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>It will keep you from the immoral woman,from the smooth tongue of a promiscuous woman.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Don’t lust for her beauty.Don’t let her coy glances seduce you.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>For a prostitute will bring you to poverty,but sleeping with another man’s wife will cost you your life.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Can a man scoop a flame into his lapand not have his clothes catch on fire?",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Can he walk on hot coalsand not blister his feet?",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So it is with the man who sleeps with another man’s wife.He who embraces her will not go unpunished.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Excuses might be found for a thiefwho steals because he is starving.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But if he is caught, he must pay back seven times what he stole,even if he has to sell everything in his house.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But the man who commits adultery is an utter fool,for he destroys himself.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He will be wounded and disgraced.His shame will never be erased.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>For the woman’s jealous husband will be furious,and he will show no mercy when he takes revenge.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>He will accept no compensation,nor be satisfied with a payoff of any size."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>Follow my advice, my son;always treasure my commands.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Obey my commands and live!Guard my instructions as you guard your own eyes.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Tie them on your fingers as a reminder.Write them deep within your heart.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Love wisdom like a sister;make insight a beloved member of your family.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Let them protect you from an affair with an immoral woman,from listening to the flattery of a promiscuous woman.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>While I was at the window of my house,looking through the curtain,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I saw some naive young men,and one in particular who lacked common sense.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He was crossing the street near the house of an immoral woman,strolling down the path by her house.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>It was at twilight, in the evening,as deep darkness fell.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The woman approached him,seductively dressed and sly of heart.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>She was the brash, rebellious type,never content to stay at home.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>She is often in the streets and markets,soliciting at every corner.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>She threw her arms around him and kissed him,and with a brazen look she said,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“I’ve just made my peace offeringsand fulfilled my vows.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>You’re the one I was looking for!I came out to find you, and here you are!",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>My bed is spread with beautiful blankets,with colored sheets of Egyptian linen.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I’ve perfumed my bedwith myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Come, let’s drink our fill of love until morning.Let’s enjoy each other’s caresses,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>for my husband is not home.He’s away on a long trip.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He has taken a wallet full of money with himand won’t return until later this month.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So she seduced him with her pretty speechand enticed him with her flattery.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He followed her at once,like an ox going to the slaughter.He was like a stag caught in a trap,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>awaiting the arrow that would pierce its heart.He was like a bird flying into a snare,little knowing it would cost him his life.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So listen to me, my sons,and pay attention to my words.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Don’t let your hearts stray away toward her.Don’t wander down her wayward path.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>For she has been the ruin of many;many men have been her victims.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Her house is the road to the grave.Her bedroom is the den of death."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>Listen as Wisdom calls out!Hear as understanding raises her voice!",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>On the hilltop along the road,she takes her stand at the crossroads.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>By the gates at the entrance to the town,on the road leading in, she cries aloud,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“I call to you, to all of you!I raise my voice to all people.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You simple people, use good judgment.You foolish people, show some understanding.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Listen to me! For I have important things to tell you.Everything I say is right,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>for I speak the truthand detest every kind of deception.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>My advice is wholesome.There is nothing devious or crooked in it.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>My words are plain to anyone with understanding,clear to those with knowledge.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Choose my instruction rather than silver,and knowledge rather than pure gold.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>For wisdom is far more valuable than rubies.Nothing you desire can compare with it.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“I, Wisdom, live together with good judgment.I know where to discover knowledge and discernment.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>All who fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will hate evil.Therefore, I hate pride and arrogance,corruption and perverse speech.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Common sense and success belong to me.Insight and strength are mine.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Because of me, kings reign,and rulers make just decrees.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Rulers lead with my help,and nobles make righteous judgments.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“I love all who love me.Those who search will surely find me.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>I have riches and honor,as well as enduring wealth and justice.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>My gifts are better than gold, even the purest gold,my wages better than sterling silver!",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>I walk in righteousness,in paths of justice.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Those who love me inherit wealth.I will fill their treasuries.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> formed me from the beginning,before he created anything else.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>I was appointed in ages past,at the very first, before the earth began.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>I was born before the oceans were created,before the springs bubbled forth their waters.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Before the mountains were formed,before the hills, I was born—",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>before he had made the earth and fieldsand the first handfuls of soil.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>I was there when he established the heavens,when he drew the horizon on the oceans.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>I was there when he set the clouds above,when he established springs deep in the earth.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>I was there when he set the limits of the seas,so they would not spread beyond their boundaries.And when he marked off the earth’s foundations,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>I was the architect at his side.I was his constant delight,rejoicing always in his presence.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And how happy I was with the world he created;how I rejoiced with the human family!",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“And so, my children, listen to me,for all who follow my ways are joyful.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Listen to my instruction and be wise.Don’t ignore it.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Joyful are those who listen to me,watching for me daily at my gates,waiting for me outside my home!",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>For whoever finds me finds lifeand receives favor from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>But those who miss me injure themselves.All who hate me love death.”"
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>Wisdom has built her house;she has carved its seven columns.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>She has prepared a great banquet,mixed the wines, and set the table.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>She has sent her servants to invite everyone to come.She calls out from the heights overlooking the city.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Come in with me,” she urges the simple.To those who lack good judgment, she says,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Come, eat my food,and drink the wine I have mixed.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Leave your simple ways behind, and begin to live;learn to use good judgment.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Anyone who rebukes a mocker will get an insult in return.Anyone who corrects the wicked will get hurt.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So don’t bother correcting mockers;they will only hate you.But correct the wise,and they will love you.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Instruct the wise,and they will be even wiser.Teach the righteous,and they will learn even more.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Fear of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is the foundation of wisdom.Knowledge of the Holy One results in good judgment.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Wisdom will multiply your daysand add years to your life.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>If you become wise, you will be the one to benefit.If you scorn wisdom, you will be the one to suffer.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The woman named Folly is brash.She is ignorant and doesn’t know it.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>She sits in her doorwayon the heights overlooking the city.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>She calls out to men going bywho are minding their own business.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Come in with me,” she urges the simple.To those who lack good judgment, she says,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“Stolen water is refreshing;food eaten in secret tastes the best!”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But little do they know that the dead are there.Her guests are in the depths of the grave."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>The proverbs of Solomon:A wise child brings joy to a father;a foolish child brings grief to a mother.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Tainted wealth has no lasting value,but right living can save your life.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will not let the godly go hungry,but he refuses to satisfy the craving of the wicked.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Lazy people are soon poor;hard workers get rich.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>A wise youth harvests in the summer,but one who sleeps during harvest is a disgrace.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The godly are showered with blessings;the words of the wicked conceal violent intentions.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>We have happy memories of the godly,but the name of a wicked person rots away.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The wise are glad to be instructed,but babbling fools fall flat on their faces.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>People with integrity walk safely,but those who follow crooked paths will be exposed.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>People who wink at wrong cause trouble,but a bold reproof promotes peace.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The words of the godly are a life-giving fountain;the words of the wicked conceal violent intentions.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Hatred stirs up quarrels,but love makes up for all offenses.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Wise words come from the lips of people with understanding,but those lacking sense will be beaten with a rod.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Wise people treasure knowledge,but the babbling of a fool invites disaster.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The wealth of the rich is their fortress;the poverty of the poor is their destruction.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The earnings of the godly enhance their lives,but evil people squander their money on sin.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>People who accept discipline are on the pathway to life,but those who ignore correction will go astray.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Hiding hatred makes you a liar;slandering others makes you a fool.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Too much talk leads to sin.Be sensible and keep your mouth shut.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The words of the godly are like sterling silver;the heart of a fool is worthless.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The words of the godly encourage many,but fools are destroyed by their lack of common sense.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The blessing of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> makes a person rich,and he adds no sorrow with it.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Doing wrong is fun for a fool,but living wisely brings pleasure to the sensible.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The fears of the wicked will be fulfilled;the hopes of the godly will be granted.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When the storms of life come, the wicked are whirled away,but the godly have a lasting foundation.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Lazy people irritate their employers,like vinegar to the teeth or smoke in the eyes.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Fear of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lengthens one’s life,but the years of the wicked are cut short.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The hopes of the godly result in happiness,but the expectations of the wicked come to nothing.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The way of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is a stronghold to those with integrity,but it destroys the wicked.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The godly will never be disturbed,but the wicked will be removed from the land.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The mouth of the godly person gives wise advice,but the tongue that deceives will be cut off.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The lips of the godly speak helpful words,but the mouth of the wicked speaks perverse words."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> detests the use of dishonest scales,but he delights in accurate weights.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Pride leads to disgrace,but with humility comes wisdom.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Honesty guides good people;dishonesty destroys treacherous people.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Riches won’t help on the day of judgment,but right living can save you from death.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The godly are directed by honesty;the wicked fall beneath their load of sin.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The godliness of good people rescues them;the ambition of treacherous people traps them.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the wicked die, their hopes die with them,for they rely on their own feeble strength.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The godly are rescued from trouble,and it falls on the wicked instead.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>With their words, the godless destroy their friends,but knowledge will rescue the righteous.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The whole city celebrates when the godly succeed;they shout for joy when the wicked die.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Upright citizens are good for a city and make it prosper,but the talk of the wicked tears it apart.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>It is foolish to belittle one’s neighbor;a sensible person keeps quiet.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>A gossip goes around telling secrets,but those who are trustworthy can keep a confidence.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Without wise leadership, a nation falls;there is safety in having many advisers.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>There’s danger in putting up security for a stranger’s debt;it’s safer not to guarantee another person’s debt.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>A gracious woman gains respect,but ruthless men gain only wealth.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Your kindness will reward you,but your cruelty will destroy you.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Evil people get rich for the moment,but the reward of the godly will last.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Godly people find life;evil people find death.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> detests people with crooked hearts,but he delights in those with integrity.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Evil people will surely be punished,but the children of the godly will go free.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>A beautiful woman who lacks discretionis like a gold ring in a pig’s snout.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The godly can look forward to a reward,while the wicked can expect only judgment.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Give freely and become more wealthy;be stingy and lose everything.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The generous will prosper;those who refresh others will themselves be refreshed.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>People curse those who hoard their grain,but they bless the one who sells in time of need.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>If you search for good, you will find favor;but if you search for evil, it will find you!",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Trust in your money and down you go!But the godly flourish like leaves in spring.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Those who bring trouble on their families inherit the wind.The fool will be a servant to the wise.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The seeds of good deeds become a tree of life;a wise person wins friends.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>If the righteous are rewarded here on earth,what will happen to wicked sinners?"
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>To learn, you must love discipline;it is stupid to hate correction.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> approves of those who are good,but he condemns those who plan wickedness.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Wickedness never brings stability,but the godly have deep roots.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>A worthy wife is a crown for her husband,but a disgraceful woman is like cancer in his bones.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The plans of the godly are just;the advice of the wicked is treacherous.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The words of the wicked are like a murderous ambush,but the words of the godly save lives.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The wicked die and disappear,but the family of the godly stands firm.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>A sensible person wins admiration,but a warped mind is despised.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Better to be an ordinary person with a servantthan to be self-important but have no food.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The godly care for their animals,but the wicked are always cruel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>A hard worker has plenty of food,but a person who chases fantasies has no sense.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Thieves are jealous of each other’s loot,but the godly are well rooted and bear their own fruit.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The wicked are trapped by their own words,but the godly escape such trouble.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Wise words bring many benefits,and hard work brings rewards.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Fools think their own way is right,but the wise listen to others.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>A fool is quick-tempered,but a wise person stays calm when insulted.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>An honest witness tells the truth;a false witness tells lies.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Some people make cutting remarks,but the words of the wise bring healing.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Truthful words stand the test of time,but lies are soon exposed.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Deceit fills hearts that are plotting evil;joy fills hearts that are planning peace!",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>No harm comes to the godly,but the wicked have their fill of trouble.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> detests lying lips,but he delights in those who tell the truth.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The wise don’t make a show of their knowledge,but fools broadcast their foolishness.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Work hard and become a leader;be lazy and become a slave.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Worry weighs a person down;an encouraging word cheers a person up.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The godly give good advice to their friends;the wicked lead them astray.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Lazy people don’t even cook the game they catch,but the diligent make use of everything they find.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The way of the godly leads to life;that path does not lead to death."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>A wise child accepts a parent’s discipline;a mocker refuses to listen to correction.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Wise words will win you a good meal,but treacherous people have an appetite for violence.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Those who control their tongue will have a long life;opening your mouth can ruin everything.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Lazy people want much but get little,but those who work hard will prosper.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The godly hate lies;the wicked cause shame and disgrace.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Godliness guards the path of the blameless,but the evil are misled by sin.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Some who are poor pretend to be rich;others who are rich pretend to be poor.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The rich can pay a ransom for their lives,but the poor won’t even get threatened.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The life of the godly is full of light and joy,but the light of the wicked will be snuffed out.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Pride leads to conflict;those who take advice are wise.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Wealth from get-rich-quick schemes quickly disappears;wealth from hard work grows over time.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Hope deferred makes the heart sick,but a dream fulfilled is a tree of life.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>People who despise advice are asking for trouble;those who respect a command will succeed.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The instruction of the wise is like a life-giving fountain;those who accept it avoid the snares of death.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>A person with good sense is respected;a treacherous person is headed for destruction.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Wise people think before they act;fools don’t—and even brag about their foolishness.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>An unreliable messenger stumbles into trouble,but a reliable messenger brings healing.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>If you ignore criticism, you will end in poverty and disgrace;if you accept correction, you will be honored.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>It is pleasant to see dreams come true,but fools refuse to turn from evil to attain them.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Walk with the wise and become wise;associate with fools and get in trouble.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Trouble chases sinners,while blessings reward the righteous.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Good people leave an inheritance to their grandchildren,but the sinner’s wealth passes to the godly.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>A poor person’s farm may produce much food,but injustice sweeps it all away.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Those who spare the rod of discipline hate their children.Those who love their children care enough to discipline them.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The godly eat to their hearts’ content,but the belly of the wicked goes hungry."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>A wise woman builds her home,but a foolish woman tears it down with her own hands.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Those who follow the right path fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;those who take the wrong path despise him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>A fool’s proud talk becomes a rod that beats him,but the words of the wise keep them safe.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Without oxen a stable stays clean,but you need a strong ox for a large harvest.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>An honest witness does not lie;a false witness breathes lies.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>A mocker seeks wisdom and never finds it,but knowledge comes easily to those with understanding.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Stay away from fools,for you won’t find knowledge on their lips.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The prudent understand where they are going,but fools deceive themselves.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Fools make fun of guilt,but the godly acknowledge it and seek reconciliation.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Each heart knows its own bitterness,and no one else can fully share its joy.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The house of the wicked will be destroyed,but the tent of the godly will flourish.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>There is a path before each person that seems right,but it ends in death.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Laughter can conceal a heavy heart,but when the laughter ends, the grief remains.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Backsliders get what they deserve;good people receive their reward.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Only simpletons believe everything they’re told!The prudent carefully consider their steps.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The wise are cautious and avoid danger;fools plunge ahead with reckless confidence.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Short-tempered people do foolish things,and schemers are hated.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Simpletons are clothed with foolishness,but the prudent are crowned with knowledge.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Evil people will bow before good people;the wicked will bow at the gates of the godly.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The poor are despised even by their neighbors,while the rich have many “friends.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>It is a sin to belittle one’s neighbor;blessed are those who help the poor.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>If you plan to do evil, you will be lost;if you plan to do good, you will receive unfailing love and faithfulness.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Work brings profit,but mere talk leads to poverty!",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Wealth is a crown for the wise;the effort of fools yields only foolishness.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>A truthful witness saves lives,but a false witness is a traitor.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Those who fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> are secure;he will be a refuge for their children.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Fear of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is a life-giving fountain;it offers escape from the snares of death.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>A growing population is a king’s glory;a prince without subjects has nothing.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>People with understanding control their anger;a hot temper shows great foolishness.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>A peaceful heart leads to a healthy body;jealousy is like cancer in the bones.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Those who oppress the poor insult their Maker,but helping the poor honors him.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The wicked are crushed by disaster,but the godly have a refuge when they die.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Wisdom is enshrined in an understanding heart;wisdom is not found among fools.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Godliness makes a nation great,but sin is a disgrace to any people.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>A king rejoices in wise servantsbut is angry with those who disgrace him."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>A gentle answer deflects anger,but harsh words make tempers flare.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The tongue of the wise makes knowledge appealing,but the mouth of a fool belches out foolishness.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is watching everywhere,keeping his eye on both the evil and the good.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Gentle words are a tree of life;a deceitful tongue crushes the spirit.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Only a fool despises a parent’s discipline;whoever learns from correction is wise.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>There is treasure in the house of the godly,but the earnings of the wicked bring trouble.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The lips of the wise give good advice;the heart of a fool has none to give.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> detests the sacrifice of the wicked,but he delights in the prayers of the upright.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> detests the way of the wicked,but he loves those who pursue godliness.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Whoever abandons the right path will be severely disciplined;whoever hates correction will die.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Even Death and Destruction hold no secrets from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.How much more does he know the human heart!",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Mockers hate to be corrected,so they stay away from the wise.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>A glad heart makes a happy face;a broken heart crushes the spirit.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>A wise person is hungry for knowledge,while the fool feeds on trash.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>For the despondent, every day brings trouble;for the happy heart, life is a continual feast.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Better to have little, with fear for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,than to have great treasure and inner turmoil.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>A bowl of vegetables with someone you loveis better than steak with someone you hate.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>A hot-tempered person starts fights;a cool-tempered person stops them.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>A lazy person’s way is blocked with briers,but the path of the upright is an open highway.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Sensible children bring joy to their father;foolish children despise their mother.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Foolishness brings joy to those with no sense;a sensible person stays on the right path.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Plans go wrong for lack of advice;many advisers bring success.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Everyone enjoys a fitting reply;it is wonderful to say the right thing at the right time!",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The path of life leads upward for the wise;they leave the grave behind.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> tears down the house of the proud,but he protects the property of widows.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> detests evil plans,but he delights in pure words.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Greed brings grief to the whole family,but those who hate bribes will live.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The heart of the godly thinks carefully before speaking;the mouth of the wicked overflows with evil words.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is far from the wicked,but he hears the prayers of the righteous.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>A cheerful look brings joy to the heart;good news makes for good health.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>If you listen to constructive criticism,you will be at home among the wise.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>If you reject discipline, you only harm yourself;but if you listen to correction, you grow in understanding.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Fear of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> teaches wisdom;humility precedes honor."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>We can make our own plans,but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gives the right answer.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>People may be pure in their own eyes,but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> examines their motives.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Commit your actions to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,and your plans will succeed.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has made everything for his own purposes,even the wicked for a day of disaster.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> detests the proud;they will surely be punished.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Unfailing love and faithfulness make atonement for sin.By fearing the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, people avoid evil.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When people’s lives please the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,even their enemies are at peace with them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Better to have little, with godliness,than to be rich and dishonest.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>We can make our plans,but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> determines our steps.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The king speaks with divine wisdom;he must never judge unfairly.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> demands accurate scales and balances;he sets the standards for fairness.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>A king detests wrongdoing,for his rule is built on justice.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The king is pleased with words from righteous lips;he loves those who speak honestly.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The anger of the king is a deadly threat;the wise will try to appease it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When the king smiles, there is life;his favor refreshes like a spring rain.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>How much better to get wisdom than gold,and good judgment than silver!",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The path of the virtuous leads away from evil;whoever follows that path is safe.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Pride goes before destruction,and haughtiness before a fall.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Better to live humbly with the poorthan to share plunder with the proud.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Those who listen to instruction will prosper;those who trust the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be joyful.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The wise are known for their understanding,and pleasant words are persuasive.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Discretion is a life-giving fountain to those who possess it,but discipline is wasted on fools.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>From a wise mind comes wise speech;the words of the wise are persuasive.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Kind words are like honey—sweet to the soul and healthy for the body.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>There is a path before each person that seems right,but it ends in death.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>It is good for workers to have an appetite;an empty stomach drives them on.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Scoundrels create trouble;their words are a destructive blaze.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>A troublemaker plants seeds of strife;gossip separates the best of friends.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Violent people mislead their companions,leading them down a harmful path.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>With narrowed eyes, people plot evil;with a smirk, they plan their mischief.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Gray hair is a crown of glory;it is gained by living a godly life.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Better to be patient than powerful;better to have self-control than to conquer a city.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>We may throw the dice,but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> determines how they fall."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>Better a dry crust eaten in peacethan a house filled with feasting—and conflict.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>A wise servant will rule over the master’s disgraceful sonand will share the inheritance of the master’s children.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Fire tests the purity of silver and gold,but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> tests the heart.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Wrongdoers eagerly listen to gossip;liars pay close attention to slander.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Those who mock the poor insult their Maker;those who rejoice at the misfortune of others will be punished.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Grandchildren are the crowning glory of the aged;parents are the pride of their children.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Eloquent words are not fitting for a fool;even less are lies fitting for a ruler.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>A bribe is like a lucky charm;whoever gives one will prosper!",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Love prospers when a fault is forgiven,but dwelling on it separates close friends.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>A single rebuke does more for a person of understandingthan a hundred lashes on the back of a fool.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Evil people are eager for rebellion,but they will be severely punished.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>It is safer to meet a bear robbed of her cubsthan to confront a fool caught in foolishness.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>If you repay good with evil,evil will never leave your house.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Starting a quarrel is like opening a floodgate,so stop before a dispute breaks out.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Acquitting the guilty and condemning the innocent—both are detestable to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>It is senseless to pay to educate a fool,since he has no heart for learning.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>A friend is always loyal,and a brother is born to help in time of need.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>It’s poor judgment to guarantee another person’s debtor put up security for a friend.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Anyone who loves to quarrel loves sin;anyone who trusts in high walls invites disaster.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The crooked heart will not prosper;the lying tongue tumbles into trouble.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>It is painful to be the parent of a fool;there is no joy for the father of a rebel.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>A cheerful heart is good medicine,but a broken spirit saps a person’s strength.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The wicked take secret bribesto pervert the course of justice.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Sensible people keep their eyes glued on wisdom,but a fool’s eyes wander to the ends of the earth.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Foolish children bring grief to their fatherand bitterness to the one who gave them birth.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>It is wrong to punish the godly for being goodor to flog leaders for being honest.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>A truly wise person uses few words;a person with understanding is even-tempered.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Even fools are thought wise when they keep silent;with their mouths shut, they seem intelligent."
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>Unfriendly people care only about themselves;they lash out at common sense.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Fools have no interest in understanding;they only want to air their own opinions.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Doing wrong leads to disgrace,and scandalous behavior brings contempt.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Wise words are like deep waters;wisdom flows from the wise like a bubbling brook.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>It is not right to acquit the guiltyor deny justice to the innocent.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Fools’ words get them into constant quarrels;they are asking for a beating.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The mouths of fools are their ruin;they trap themselves with their lips.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Rumors are dainty morselsthat sink deep into one’s heart.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>A lazy person is as bad assomeone who destroys things.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is a strong fortress;the godly run to him and are safe.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The rich think of their wealth as a strong defense;they imagine it to be a high wall of safety.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Haughtiness goes before destruction;humility precedes honor.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Spouting off before listening to the factsis both shameful and foolish.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The human spirit can endure a sick body,but who can bear a crushed spirit?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Intelligent people are always ready to learn.Their ears are open for knowledge.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Giving a gift can open doors;it gives access to important people!",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The first to speak in court sounds right—until the cross-examination begins.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Flipping a coin can end arguments;it settles disputes between powerful opponents.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>An offended friend is harder to win back than a fortified city.Arguments separate friends like a gate locked with bars.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Wise words satisfy like a good meal;the right words bring satisfaction.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The tongue can bring death or life;those who love to talk will reap the consequences.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The man who finds a wife finds a treasure,and he receives favor from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The poor plead for mercy;the rich answer with insults.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>There are “friends” who destroy each other,but a real friend sticks closer than a brother."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>Better to be poor and honestthan to be dishonest and a fool.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Enthusiasm without knowledge is no good;haste makes mistakes.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>People ruin their lives by their own foolishnessand then are angry at the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Wealth makes many “friends”;poverty drives them all away.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>A false witness will not go unpunished,nor will a liar escape.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Many seek favors from a ruler;everyone is the friend of a person who gives gifts!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The relatives of the poor despise them;how much more will their friends avoid them!Though the poor plead with them,their friends are gone.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>To acquire wisdom is to love yourself;people who cherish understanding will prosper.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>A false witness will not go unpunished,and a liar will be destroyed.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>It isn’t right for a fool to live in luxuryor for a slave to rule over princes!",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Sensible people control their temper;they earn respect by overlooking wrongs.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The king’s anger is like a lion’s roar,but his favor is like dew on the grass.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>A foolish child is a calamity to a father;a quarrelsome wife is as annoying as constant dripping.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Fathers can give their sons an inheritance of houses and wealth,but only the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> can give an understanding wife.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Lazy people sleep soundly,but idleness leaves them hungry.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Keep the commandments and keep your life;despising them leads to death.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>If you help the poor, you are lending to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—and he will repay you!",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Discipline your children while there is hope.Otherwise you will ruin their lives.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Hot-tempered people must pay the penalty.If you rescue them once, you will have to do it again.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Get all the advice and instruction you can,so you will be wise the rest of your life.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>You can make many plans,but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s purpose will prevail.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Loyalty makes a person attractive.It is better to be poor than dishonest.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Fear of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> leads to life,bringing security and protection from harm.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Lazy people take food in their handbut don’t even lift it to their mouth.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>If you punish a mocker, the simpleminded will learn a lesson;if you correct the wise, they will be all the wiser.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Children who mistreat their father or chase away their motherare an embarrassment and a public disgrace.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>If you stop listening to instruction, my child,you will turn your back on knowledge.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>A corrupt witness makes a mockery of justice;the mouth of the wicked gulps down evil.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Punishment is made for mockers,and the backs of fools are made to be beaten."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>Wine produces mockers; alcohol leads to brawls.Those led astray by drink cannot be wise.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The king’s fury is like a lion’s roar;to rouse his anger is to risk your life.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Avoiding a fight is a mark of honor;only fools insist on quarreling.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Those too lazy to plow in the right seasonwill have no food at the harvest.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Though good advice lies deep within the heart,a person with understanding will draw it out.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Many will say they are loyal friends,but who can find one who is truly reliable?",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The godly walk with integrity;blessed are their children who follow them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When a king sits in judgment, he weighs all the evidence,distinguishing the bad from the good.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Who can say, “I have cleansed my heart;I am pure and free from sin”?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>False weights and unequal measures—the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> detests double standards of every kind.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Even children are known by the way they act,whether their conduct is pure, and whether it is right.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Ears to hear and eyes to see—both are gifts from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>If you love sleep, you will end in poverty.Keep your eyes open, and there will be plenty to eat!",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The buyer haggles over the price, saying, “It’s worthless,”then brags about getting a bargain!",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Wise words are more valuablethan much gold and many rubies.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Get security from someone who guarantees a stranger’s debt.Get a deposit if he does it for foreigners.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Stolen bread tastes sweet,but it turns to gravel in the mouth.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Plans succeed through good counsel;don’t go to war without wise advice.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>A gossip goes around telling secrets,so don’t hang around with chatterers.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>If you insult your father or mother,your light will be snuffed out in total darkness.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>An inheritance obtained too early in lifeis not a blessing in the end.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Don’t say, “I will get even for this wrong.”Wait for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to handle the matter.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> detests double standards;he is not pleased by dishonest scales.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> directs our steps,so why try to understand everything along the way?",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Don’t trap yourself by making a rash promise to Godand only later counting the cost.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>A wise king scatters the wicked like wheat,then runs his threshing wheel over them.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s light penetrates the human spirit,exposing every hidden motive.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Unfailing love and faithfulness protect the king;his throne is made secure through love.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The glory of the young is their strength;the gray hair of experience is the splendor of the old.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Physical punishment cleanses away evil;such discipline purifies the heart."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>The king’s heart is like a stream of water directed by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;he guides it wherever he pleases.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>People may be right in their own eyes,but the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> examines their heart.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is more pleased when we do what is right and justthan when we offer him sacrifices.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Haughty eyes, a proud heart,and evil actions are all sin.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Good planning and hard work lead to prosperity,but hasty shortcuts lead to poverty.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Wealth created by a lying tongueis a vanishing mist and a deadly trap.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The violence of the wicked sweeps them away,because they refuse to do what is just.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The guilty walk a crooked path;the innocent travel a straight road.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>It’s better to live alone in the corner of an atticthan with a quarrelsome wife in a lovely home.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Evil people desire evil;their neighbors get no mercy from them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>If you punish a mocker, the simpleminded become wise;if you instruct the wise, they will be all the wiser.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The Righteous One knows what is going on in the homes of the wicked;he will bring disaster on them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Those who shut their ears to the cries of the poorwill be ignored in their own time of need.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>A secret gift calms anger;a bribe under the table pacifies fury.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Justice is a joy to the godly,but it terrifies evildoers.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The person who strays from common sensewill end up in the company of the dead.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Those who love pleasure become poor;those who love wine and luxury will never be rich.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The wicked are punished in place of the godly,and traitors in place of the honest.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>It’s better to live alone in the desertthan with a quarrelsome, complaining wife.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The wise have wealth and luxury,but fools spend whatever they get.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Whoever pursues righteousness and unfailing lovewill find life, righteousness, and honor.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The wise conquer the city of the strongand level the fortress in which they trust.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Watch your tongue and keep your mouth shut,and you will stay out of trouble.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Mockers are proud and haughty;they act with boundless arrogance.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Despite their desires, the lazy will come to ruin,for their hands refuse to work.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Some people are always greedy for more,but the godly love to give!",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The sacrifice of an evil person is detestable,especially when it is offered with wrong motives.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>A false witness will be cut off,but a credible witness will be allowed to speak.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The wicked bluff their way through,but the virtuous think before they act.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>No human wisdom or understanding or plancan stand against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The horse is prepared for the day of battle,but the victory belongs to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>Choose a good reputation over great riches;being held in high esteem is better than silver or gold.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The rich and poor have this in common:The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made them both.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>A prudent person foresees danger and takes precautions.The simpleton goes blindly on and suffers the consequences.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>True humility and fear of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>lead to riches, honor, and long life.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Corrupt people walk a thorny, treacherous road;whoever values life will avoid it.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Direct your children onto the right path,and when they are older, they will not leave it.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Just as the rich rule the poor,so the borrower is servant to the lender.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Those who plant injustice will harvest disaster,and their reign of terror will come to an end.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Blessed are those who are generous,because they feed the poor.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Throw out the mocker, and fighting goes, too.Quarrels and insults will disappear.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Whoever loves a pure heart and gracious speechwill have the king as a friend.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> preserves those with knowledge,but he ruins the plans of the treacherous.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The lazy person claims, “There’s a lion out there!If I go outside, I might be killed!”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The mouth of an immoral woman is a dangerous trap;those who make the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> angry will fall into it.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>A youngster’s heart is filled with foolishness,but physical discipline will drive it far away.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>A person who gets ahead by oppressing the pooror by showering gifts on the rich will end in poverty.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Listen to the words of the wise;apply your heart to my instruction.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>For it is good to keep these sayings in your heartand always ready on your lips.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>I am teaching you today—yes, you—so you will trust in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>I have written thirty sayings for you,filled with advice and knowledge.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>In this way, you may know the truthand take an accurate report to those who sent you.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Don’t rob the poor just because you can,or exploit the needy in court.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is their defender.He will ruin anyone who ruins them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Don’t befriend angry peopleor associate with hot-tempered people,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>or you will learn to be like themand endanger your soul.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Don’t agree to guarantee another person’s debtor put up security for someone else.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>If you can’t pay it,even your bed will be snatched from under you.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Don’t cheat your neighbor by moving the ancient boundary markersset up by previous generations.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Do you see any truly competent workers?They will serve kingsrather than working for ordinary people."
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>While dining with a ruler,pay attention to what is put before you.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>If you are a big eater,put a knife to your throat;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>don’t desire all the delicacies,for he might be trying to trick you.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Don’t wear yourself out trying to get rich.Be wise enough to know when to quit.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>In the blink of an eye wealth disappears,for it will sprout wingsand fly away like an eagle.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Don’t eat with people who are stingy;don’t desire their delicacies.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They are always thinking about how much it costs.“Eat and drink,” they say, but they don’t mean it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You will throw up what little you’ve eaten,and your compliments will be wasted.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Don’t waste your breath on fools,for they will despise the wisest advice.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Don’t cheat your neighbor by moving the ancient boundary markers;don’t take the land of defenseless orphans.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>For their Redeemer is strong;he himself will bring their charges against you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Commit yourself to instruction;listen carefully to words of knowledge.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Don’t fail to discipline your children.The rod of punishment won’t kill them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Physical disciplinemay well save them from death.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>My child, if your heart is wise,my own heart will rejoice!",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Everything in me will celebratewhen you speak what is right.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Don’t envy sinners,but always continue to fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>You will be rewarded for this;your hope will not be disappointed.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>My child, listen and be wise:Keep your heart on the right course.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Do not carouse with drunkardsor feast with gluttons,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>for they are on their way to poverty,and too much sleep clothes them in rags.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Listen to your father, who gave you life,and don’t despise your mother when she is old.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Get the truth and never sell it;also get wisdom, discipline, and good judgment.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The father of godly children has cause for joy.What a pleasure to have children who are wise.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So give your father and mother joy!May she who gave you birth be happy.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>O my son, give me your heart.May your eyes take delight in following my ways.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>A prostitute is a dangerous trap;a promiscuous woman is as dangerous as falling into a narrow well.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>She hides and waits like a robber,eager to make more men unfaithful.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Who has anguish? Who has sorrow?Who is always fighting? Who is always complaining?Who has unnecessary bruises? Who has bloodshot eyes?",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>It is the one who spends long hours in the taverns,trying out new drinks.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Don’t gaze at the wine, seeing how red it is,how it sparkles in the cup, how smoothly it goes down.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>For in the end it bites like a poisonous snake;it stings like a viper.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>You will see hallucinations,and you will say crazy things.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>You will stagger like a sailor tossed at sea,clinging to a swaying mast.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And you will say, “They hit me, but I didn’t feel it.I didn’t even know it when they beat me up.When will I wake upso I can look for another drink?”"
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>Don’t envy evil peopleor desire their company.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>For their hearts plot violence,and their words always stir up trouble.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>A house is built by wisdomand becomes strong through good sense.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Through knowledge its rooms are filledwith all sorts of precious riches and valuables.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The wise are mightier than the strong,and those with knowledge grow stronger and stronger.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So don’t go to war without wise guidance;victory depends on having many advisers.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Wisdom is too lofty for fools.Among leaders at the city gate, they have nothing to say.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>A person who plans evilwill get a reputation as a troublemaker.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The schemes of a fool are sinful;everyone detests a mocker.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>If you fail under pressure,your strength is too small.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Rescue those who are unjustly sentenced to die;save them as they stagger to their death.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Don’t excuse yourself by saying, “Look, we didn’t know.”For God understands all hearts, and he sees you.He who guards your soul knows you knew.He will repay all people as their actions deserve.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>My child, eat honey, for it is good,and the honeycomb is sweet to the taste.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>In the same way, wisdom is sweet to your soul.If you find it, you will have a bright future,and your hopes will not be cut short.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Don’t wait in ambush at the home of the godly,and don’t raid the house where the godly live.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The godly may trip seven times, but they will get up again.But one disaster is enough to overthrow the wicked.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Don’t rejoice when your enemies fall;don’t be happy when they stumble.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be displeased with youand will turn his anger away from them.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Don’t fret because of evildoers;don’t envy the wicked.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>For evil people have no future;the light of the wicked will be snuffed out.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>My child, fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the king.Don’t associate with rebels,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>for disaster will hit them suddenly.Who knows what punishment will comefrom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the king?",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Here are some further sayings of the wise:It is wrong to show favoritism when passing judgment.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>A judge who says to the wicked, “You are innocent,”will be cursed by many people and denounced by the nations.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But it will go well for those who convict the guilty;rich blessings will be showered on them.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>An honest answeris like a kiss of friendship.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Do your planning and prepare your fieldsbefore building your house.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Don’t testify against your neighbors without cause;don’t lie about them.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And don’t say, “Now I can pay them back for what they’ve done to me!I’ll get even with them!”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>I walked by the field of a lazy person,the vineyard of one with no common sense.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>I saw that it was overgrown with nettles.It was covered with weeds,and its walls were broken down.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then, as I looked and thought about it,I learned this lesson:",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>A little extra sleep, a little more slumber,a little folding of the hands to rest—",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>then poverty will pounce on you like a bandit;scarcity will attack you like an armed robber."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span>These are more proverbs of Solomon, collected by the advisers of King Hezekiah of Judah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>It is God’s privilege to conceal thingsand the king’s privilege to discover them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>No one can comprehend the height of heaven, the depth of the earth,or all that goes on in the king’s mind!",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Remove the impurities from silver,and the sterling will be ready for the silversmith.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Remove the wicked from the king’s court,and his reign will be made secure by justice.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Don’t demand an audience with the kingor push for a place among the great.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>It’s better to wait for an invitation to the head tablethan to be sent away in public disgrace.Just because you’ve seen something,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>don’t be in a hurry to go to court.For what will you do in the endif your neighbor deals you a shameful defeat?",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>When arguing with your neighbor,don’t betray another person’s secret.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Others may accuse you of gossip,and you will never regain your good reputation.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Timely advice is lovely,like golden apples in a silver basket.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>To one who listens, valid criticismis like a gold earring or other gold jewelry.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Trustworthy messengers refresh like snow in summer.They revive the spirit of their employer.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>A person who promises a gift but doesn’t give itis like clouds and wind that bring no rain.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Patience can persuade a prince,and soft speech can break bones.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Do you like honey?Don’t eat too much, or it will make you sick!",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Don’t visit your neighbors too often,or you will wear out your welcome.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Telling lies about othersis as harmful as hitting them with an ax,wounding them with a sword,or shooting them with a sharp arrow.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Putting confidence in an unreliable person in times of troubleis like chewing with a broken tooth or walking on a lame foot.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Singing cheerful songs to a person with a heavy heartis like taking someone’s coat in cold weatheror pouring vinegar in a wound.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>If your enemies are hungry, give them food to eat.If they are thirsty, give them water to drink.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>You will heap burning coals of shame on their heads,and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will reward you.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>As surely as a north wind brings rain,so a gossiping tongue causes anger!",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>It’s better to live alone in the corner of an atticthan with a quarrelsome wife in a lovely home.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Good news from far awayis like cold water to the thirsty.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>If the godly give in to the wicked,it’s like polluting a fountain or muddying a spring.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>It’s not good to eat too much honey,and it’s not good to seek honors for yourself.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>A person without self-controlis like a city with broken-down walls."
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>Honor is no more associated with foolsthan snow with summer or rain with harvest.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Like a fluttering sparrow or a darting swallow,an undeserved curse will not land on its intended victim.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Guide a horse with a whip, a donkey with a bridle,and a fool with a rod to his back!",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Don’t answer the foolish arguments of fools,or you will become as foolish as they are.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Be sure to answer the foolish arguments of fools,or they will become wise in their own estimation.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Trusting a fool to convey a messageis like cutting off one’s feet or drinking poison!",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>A proverb in the mouth of a foolis as useless as a paralyzed leg.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Honoring a foolis as foolish as tying a stone to a slingshot.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>A proverb in the mouth of a foolis like a thorny branch brandished by a drunk.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>An employer who hires a fool or a bystanderis like an archer who shoots at random.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>As a dog returns to its vomit,so a fool repeats his foolishness.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>There is more hope for foolsthan for people who think they are wise.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The lazy person claims, “There’s a lion on the road!Yes, I’m sure there’s a lion out there!”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>As a door swings back and forth on its hinges,so the lazy person turns over in bed.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Lazy people take food in their handbut don’t even lift it to their mouth.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Lazy people consider themselves smarterthan seven wise counselors.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Interfering in someone else’s argumentis as foolish as yanking a dog’s ears.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Just as damagingas a madman shooting a deadly weapon",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>is someone who lies to a friendand then says, “I was only joking.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Fire goes out without wood,and quarrels disappear when gossip stops.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>A quarrelsome person starts fightsas easily as hot embers light charcoal or fire lights wood.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Rumors are dainty morselsthat sink deep into one’s heart.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Smooth words may hide a wicked heart,just as a pretty glaze covers a clay pot.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>People may cover their hatred with pleasant words,but they’re deceiving you.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>They pretend to be kind, but don’t believe them.Their hearts are full of many evils.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>While their hatred may be concealed by trickery,their wrongdoing will be exposed in public.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>If you set a trap for others,you will get caught in it yourself.If you roll a boulder down on others,it will crush you instead.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>A lying tongue hates its victims,and flattering words cause ruin."
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span>Don’t brag about tomorrow,since you don’t know what the day will bring.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Let someone else praise you, not your own mouth—a stranger, not your own lips.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>A stone is heavy and sand is weighty,but the resentment caused by a fool is even heavier.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Anger is cruel, and wrath is like a flood,but jealousy is even more dangerous.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>An open rebukeis better than hidden love!",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Wounds from a sincere friendare better than many kisses from an enemy.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>A person who is full refuses honey,but even bitter food tastes sweet to the hungry.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>A person who strays from homeis like a bird that strays from its nest.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The heartfelt counsel of a friendis as sweet as perfume and incense.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Never abandon a friend—either yours or your father’s.When disaster strikes, you won’t have to ask your brother for assistance.It’s better to go to a neighbor than to a brother who lives far away.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Be wise, my child, and make my heart glad.Then I will be able to answer my critics.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>A prudent person foresees danger and takes precautions.The simpleton goes blindly on and suffers the consequences.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Get security from someone who guarantees a stranger’s debt.Get a deposit if he does it for foreigners.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>A loud and cheerful greeting early in the morningwill be taken as a curse!",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>A quarrelsome wife is as annoyingas constant dripping on a rainy day.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Stopping her complaints is like trying to stop the windor trying to hold something with greased hands.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>As iron sharpens iron,so a friend sharpens a friend.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>As workers who tend a fig tree are allowed to eat the fruit,so workers who protect their employer’s interests will be rewarded.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>As a face is reflected in water,so the heart reflects the real person.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Just as Death and Destruction are never satisfied,so human desire is never satisfied.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Fire tests the purity of silver and gold,but a person is tested by being praised.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>You cannot separate fools from their foolishness,even though you grind them like grain with mortar and pestle.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Know the state of your flocks,and put your heart into caring for your herds,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>for riches don’t last forever,and the crown might not be passed to the next generation.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>After the hay is harvested and the new crop appearsand the mountain grasses are gathered in,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>your sheep will provide wool for clothing,and your goats will provide the price of a field.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And you will have enough goats’ milk for yourself,your family, and your servant girls."
		},
		"28": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">28 </span>The wicked run away when no one is chasing them,but the godly are as bold as lions.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When there is moral rot within a nation, its government topples easily.But wise and knowledgeable leaders bring stability.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>A poor person who oppresses the pooris like a pounding rain that destroys the crops.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>To reject the law is to praise the wicked;to obey the law is to fight them.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Evil people don’t understand justice,but those who follow the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> understand completely.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Better to be poor and honestthan to be dishonest and rich.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Young people who obey the law are wise;those with wild friends bring shame to their parents.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Income from charging high interest rateswill end up in the pocket of someone who is kind to the poor.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>God detests the prayersof a person who ignores the law.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Those who lead good people along an evil pathwill fall into their own trap,but the honest will inherit good things.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Rich people may think they are wise,but a poor person with discernment can see right through them.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When the godly succeed, everyone is glad.When the wicked take charge, people go into hiding.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>People who conceal their sins will not prosper,but if they confess and turn from them, they will receive mercy.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Blessed are those who fear to do wrong,but the stubborn are headed for serious trouble.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>A wicked ruler is as dangerous to the pooras a roaring lion or an attacking bear.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>A ruler with no understanding will oppress his people,but one who hates corruption will have a long life.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>A murderer’s tormented conscience will drive him into the grave.Don’t protect him!",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The blameless will be rescued from harm,but the crooked will be suddenly destroyed.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>A hard worker has plenty of food,but a person who chases fantasies ends up in poverty.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The trustworthy person will get a rich reward,but a person who wants quick riches will get into trouble.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Showing partiality is never good,yet some will do wrong for a mere piece of bread.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Greedy people try to get rich quickbut don’t realize they’re headed for poverty.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>In the end, people appreciate honest criticismfar more than flattery.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Anyone who steals from his father and motherand says, “What’s wrong with that?”is no better than a murderer.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Greed causes fighting;trusting the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> leads to prosperity.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Those who trust their own insight are foolish,but anyone who walks in wisdom is safe.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Whoever gives to the poor will lack nothing,but those who close their eyes to poverty will be cursed.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>When the wicked take charge, people go into hiding.When the wicked meet disaster, the godly flourish."
		},
		"29": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">29 </span>Whoever stubbornly refuses to accept criticismwill suddenly be destroyed beyond recovery.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When the godly are in authority, the people rejoice.But when the wicked are in power, they groan.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The man who loves wisdom brings joy to his father,but if he hangs around with prostitutes, his wealth is wasted.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>A just king gives stability to his nation,but one who demands bribes destroys it.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>To flatter friendsis to lay a trap for their feet.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Evil people are trapped by sin,but the righteous escape, shouting for joy.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The godly care about the rights of the poor;the wicked don’t care at all.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Mockers can get a whole town agitated,but the wise will calm anger.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>If a wise person takes a fool to court,there will be ranting and ridicule but no satisfaction.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The bloodthirsty hate blameless people,but the upright seek to help them.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Fools vent their anger,but the wise quietly hold it back.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>If a ruler pays attention to liars,all his advisers will be wicked.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The poor and the oppressor have this in common—the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gives sight to the eyes of both.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>If a king judges the poor fairly,his throne will last forever.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>To discipline a child produces wisdom,but a mother is disgraced by an undisciplined child.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When the wicked are in authority, sin flourishes,but the godly will live to see their downfall.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Discipline your children, and they will give you peace of mindand will make your heart glad.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When people do not accept divine guidance, they run wild.But whoever obeys the law is joyful.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Words alone will not discipline a servant;the words may be understood, but they are not heeded.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>There is more hope for a foolthan for someone who speaks without thinking.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>A servant pampered from childhoodwill become a rebel.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>An angry person starts fights;a hot-tempered person commits all kinds of sin.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Pride ends in humiliation,while humility brings honor.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>If you assist a thief, you only hurt yourself.You are sworn to tell the truth, but you dare not testify.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Fearing people is a dangerous trap,but trusting the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> means safety.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Many seek the ruler’s favor,but justice comes from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The righteous despise the unjust;the wicked despise the godly."
		},
		"30": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">30 </span>The sayings of Agur son of Jakeh contain this message.I am weary, O God;I am weary and worn out, O God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I am too stupid to be human,and I lack common sense.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I have not mastered human wisdom,nor do I know the Holy One.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Who but God goes up to heaven and comes back down?Who holds the wind in his fists?Who wraps up the oceans in his cloak?Who has created the whole wide world?What is his name—and his son’s name?Tell me if you know!",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Every word of God proves true.He is a shield to all who come to him for protection.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Do not add to his words,or he may rebuke you and expose you as a liar.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>O God, I beg two favors from you;let me have them before I die.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>First, help me never to tell a lie.Second, give me neither poverty nor riches!Give me just enough to satisfy my needs.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For if I grow rich, I may deny you and say, “Who is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”And if I am too poor, I may steal and thus insult God’s holy name.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Never slander a worker to the employer,or the person will curse you, and you will pay for it.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Some people curse their fatherand do not thank their mother.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They are pure in their own eyes,but they are filthy and unwashed.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>They look proudly around,casting disdainful glances.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They have teeth like swordsand fangs like knives.They devour the poor from the earthand the needy from among humanity.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The leech has two suckersthat cry out, “More, more!”There are three things that are never satisfied—no, four that never say, “Enough!”:",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>the grave,the barren womb,the thirsty desert,the blazing fire.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The eye that mocks a fatherand despises a mother’s instructionswill be plucked out by ravens of the valleyand eaten by vultures.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>There are three things that amaze me—no, four things that I don’t understand:",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>how an eagle glides through the sky,how a snake slithers on a rock,how a ship navigates the ocean,how a man loves a woman.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>An adulterous woman consumes a man,then wipes her mouth and says, “What’s wrong with that?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>There are three things that make the earth tremble—no, four it cannot endure:",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>a slave who becomes a king,an overbearing fool who prospers,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>a bitter woman who finally gets a husband,a servant girl who supplants her mistress.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>There are four things on earth that are small but unusually wise:",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Ants—they aren’t strong,but they store up food all summer.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Hyraxes—they aren’t powerful,but they make their homes among the rocks.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Locusts—they have no king,but they march in formation.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Lizards—they are easy to catch,but they are found even in kings’ palaces.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>There are three things that walk with stately stride—no, four that strut about:",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>the lion, king of animals, who won’t turn aside for anything,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><span class=\"indent-1-breaks\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>the strutting rooster,the male goat,a king as he leads his army.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>If you have been a fool by being proud or plotting evil,cover your mouth in shame.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>As the beating of cream yields butterand striking the nose causes bleeding,so stirring up anger causes quarrels."
		},
		"31": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">31 </span>The sayings of King Lemuel contain this message, which his mother taught him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>O my son, O son of my womb,O son of my vows,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>do not waste your strength on women,on those who ruin kings.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>It is not for kings, O Lemuel, to guzzle wine.Rulers should not crave alcohol.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For if they drink, they may forget the lawand not give justice to the oppressed.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Alcohol is for the dying,and wine for those in bitter distress.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Let them drink to forget their povertyand remember their troubles no more.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Speak up for those who cannot speak for themselves;ensure justice for those being crushed.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Yes, speak up for the poor and helpless,and see that they get justice.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Who can find a virtuous and capable wife?She is more precious than rubies.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Her husband can trust her,and she will greatly enrich his life.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>She brings him good, not harm,all the days of her life.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>She finds wool and flaxand busily spins it.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>She is like a merchant’s ship,bringing her food from afar.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>She gets up before dawn to prepare breakfast for her householdand plan the day’s work for her servant girls.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>She goes to inspect a field and buys it;with her earnings she plants a vineyard.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>She is energetic and strong,a hard worker.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>She makes sure her dealings are profitable;her lamp burns late into the night.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Her hands are busy spinning thread,her fingers twisting fiber.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>She extends a helping hand to the poorand opens her arms to the needy.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>She has no fear of winter for her household,for everyone has warm clothes.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>She makes her own bedspreads.She dresses in fine linen and purple gowns.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Her husband is well known at the city gates,where he sits with the other civic leaders.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>She makes belted linen garmentsand sashes to sell to the merchants.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>She is clothed with strength and dignity,and she laughs without fear of the future.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When she speaks, her words are wise,and she gives instructions with kindness.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>She carefully watches everything in her householdand suffers nothing from laziness.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Her children stand and bless her.Her husband praises her:",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“There are many virtuous and capable women in the world,but you surpass them all!”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Charm is deceptive, and beauty does not last;but a woman who fears the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be greatly praised.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Reward her for all she has done.Let her deeds publicly declare her praise."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;